Used as often in the peasant's home as the dungeon's dark, these simple concoctions are common throughout Faerun.

Greenfish are abundant in the seas that lap the coast of Nordock. While bland themselves, a concoction of pepper and other spices brings out a surprisingly tangy and pleasant flavor. This fish counts as a single food serving for resting purposes.
A large piece of meat has dislodged from the creature. It would not be wise to eat it. Perhaps if you cook it on a campfire it would be safe to consume.

Welcome to the City of Benzor
Welcome to the great west coast city of Benzor.

All travellers through this North Gate...be advised:
The local wildlife includes not only bears but giant spiders. Also, many kobolds and other worse creatures have been spotted in the swampy lands east of the wooded area.
Please also be advised that the savage Zhengi have taken a liking to the taste of human flesh. Until such a time that the Duke can collect a force to eliminate them, we ask that all travel to the North be postponed.
Henroid Tucker Captain, Benzor Militia
All races welcome to work on tradeskills development here.

This house is for players to purchase and furnish. Only one player at a time can actually "own" the house, but when he or she logs off, someone else can claim it for a time. The furniture bought is saved on a deed. See a housing merchant to buy a key and furniture.
